  "prompt": "Is Governor of RBI (Reserve Bank of India) a constitutional post?",
  "response": "No, the Governor of the Reserve Bank of India (RBI) does not hold a constitutional post. The position of the RBI Governor is established under the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934. This act provides the statutory framework for the functioning and governance of the RBI, which is India's central bank. While the role is crucial to the economic and financial stability of the country, it is not specifically mentioned in the Constitution of India.",
